{"key":"post-9982143","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9982143</id>\n<content>Don't use distilled for anything but agar which remains sterile all the time anyway.&amp;nbsp; Distilled water should not be used to make up substrates or for misting, etc.&amp;nbsp; Well or tap water is fine.&amp;nbsp; If you're worried, use spring water, but I hate paying big money for what I have coming out of the faucet, and then there's the plastic waste from bottled water which isn't ecologically sound.&amp;nbsp; If there's a creek or river nearby, that works great too.&amp;nbsp; You're going to sterilize it anyway, so don't worry about contaminants.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9982683</next>\n<prev>9981365</prev>\n<first>9980947</first>\n<last>9987097</last>\n<when>1237235078</when>\n<utime>03/16/09 11:24 PM</utime>\n</post>"}